data.text: Of, relating to, or capable of speed equal to or exceeding five times the speed of sound.
data.attributionText: from The American HeritageÂ® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.

data.text: Pertaining to or moving at a speed greatly in excess of the speed of sound, usually meaning greater than mach 5. All speeds in excess of the speed of sound are <contr>supersonic</contr>, but to be <ex>hypersonic</ex> requires even higher speed.
data.attributionText: from the GNU version of the Collaborative International Dictionary of English.

data.text: <xref>equal</xref> to, or <xref>greater</xref> than, or capable of achieving, five times the <xref>speed of sound</xref>.
data.attributionText: from Wiktionary, Creative Commons Attribution/Share-Alike License.

data.text: far enough above the speed of sound so as to cause significant differences in behaviour due to chemical reactions or disassociation of the air.
